cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a solution using machine learning and acoustic surveillance technologies for rainforest conservation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Sound (cs.SD) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed solution involves the use of convolutional neural network (CNN) models for sound classification, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the possibility of using automated machine learning, which is a sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
